data.chText: （通常指码放整齐的）一叠，一摞，一堆
data.enText: a pile of sth, usually neatly arranged

data.chText: 一摞书
data.enText: a stack of books

data.chText: 一套高保真组合音响
data.enText: a stack hi-fi system (= where radio, CD player, etc. are arranged on top of each other)

data.chText: 大量；许多；一大堆
data.enText: a large number or amount of sth; a lot of sth

data.chText: 许多钱
data.enText: stacks of money

data.chText: 家里有一大堆信等你拆呢。
data.enText: There's a stack of unopened mail waiting for you at the house.

data.chText: 我有一大堆活儿要做。
data.enText: I've got stacks of work to do.

data.chText: （尤指工厂的）大烟囱
data.enText: a tall chimney , especially on a factory

data.chText: （图书馆中贮藏使用频率较低的书的）书库
data.enText: the part of a library, sometimes not open to the public, where books that are not often needed are stored

data.chText: 堆栈
data.enText: a way of storing information in a computer in which the most recently stored item is the first to be retrieved (= found or got back)

data.chText: （使）放成整齐的一叠（或一摞、一堆）
data.enText: to arrange objects neatly in a pile; to be arranged in this way

data.chText: 把箱子摞起来
data.enText: to stack boxes

data.chText: 靠墙码放着的木头
data.enText: logs stacked up against a wall

data.chText: 这些椅子能摞起来吗？
data.enText: Do these chairs stack?

data.chText: 可摞在一起的椅子
data.enText: stacking chairs

data.chText: 使成叠（或成摞、成堆）地放在…；使码放在…
data.enText: to fill sth with piles of things

data.chText: 他们正忙着摆货物上架呢。
data.enText: They were busy stacking the shelves with goods.

data.chText: （令飞机）分层盘旋等待着陆
data.enText: if aircraft stack (up) or are stacked (up) over an airport, there are several flying around waiting for their turn to land
stack up

data.chText: 积聚成一大堆（或一长排等）
data.enText: to keep increasing in quantity until there is a large pile, a long line, etc.

data.chText: 公共汽车后面的汽车很快排成了长龙。
data.enText: Cars quickly stacked up behind the bus.

data.chText: （与其他人或事物）相比；比得上

before.chText: 尤用于疑问句或否定句
before.enText: used especially in questions or in negatives

data.enText: to compare with sb/sth else; to be as good as sb/sth else

data.chText: 咱们让他干这活儿试试，看看他比别人干得怎么样。
data.enText: Let's try him in the job and see how he stacks up.

data.chText: 活动房屋怎么也比不上传统的房屋。
data.enText: A mobile home simply doesn't stack up against a traditional house.

data.chText: 看来合理；讲得通；合乎情理
data.enText: to seem reasonable; to make sense

data.chText: 那不可能是对的，简直不合情理。
data.enText: That can't be right. It just doesn't stack up.

synonyms.bx: 通常指把东西杂乱地堆集在一起，不强调整齐。

ex.chText: 她把面包和苹果往篮子里堆。

ex.chText: 他把盒子一个个地摞起来。

ex.chText: 她女儿帮她把衣服一件件叠放进手提箱中。
ex.enText: Her daughter helped her pile clothes into the suitcase.

synonyms.bx: 既可指把东西较整齐地叠放起来，又可指把东西杂乱地堆起来。

ex.chText: 把桌子上的杂志摞起来。
ex.enText: Stack the magazines on the table.

ex.chText: 售货员给商品标价，然后把它们叠放到货架上。
ex.enText: The assistants priced the items and stacked them on the shelves.

synonyms.bx: 指把东西较整齐地堆放起来。

tr: a storage device that handles data so that the next item to be retrieved is the item most recently stored (LIFO)
a large tall chimney through which combustion gases and smoke can be evacuated
a list in which the next item to be removed is the item most recently stored (LIFO)
(often followed by `of') a large number or amount or extent
example: he made a mint on the stock market
see the rest of the winners in our huge passel of photos

tr: arrange the order of so as to increase one's winning chances

example: stack your books up on the shelves

value.def: A stack of things is a pile of them.

example.ex: There were stacks of books on the bedside table and floor.
example.tran: 床头桌和地板上有几摞书。

value.def: If you stack a number of things, you arrange them in neat piles.

example.ex: Mme Cathiard was stacking the clean bottles in crates...
example.tran: 凯西亚德夫人正在将干净的瓶子整齐地码放在板条箱里。

example.ex: They are stacked neatly in piles of three.
example.tran: 它们每 3 个一组被整齐地码放在一起。

example.ex: He ordered them to stack up pillows behind his back.
example.tran: 他命令他们把几个枕头叠放在自己的背后。

example.ex: ...plates of delicious food stacked up on the counters.
example.tran: 整齐地堆放在柜台上的一盘盘美味佳肴

value.def: If you say that someone has stacks of something, you mean that they have a lot of it.

example.ex: If the job's that good, you'll have stacks of money.
example.tran: 如果这个工作真有那么好，你将会赚很多钱。

value.def: If someone in authority stacks an organization or body, they fill it with their own supporters so that the decisions it makes will be the ones they want it to make.

example.ex: They said they were going to stack the court with anti-abortion judges...
example.tran: 他们说将会往法院中安排一些反对堕胎的法官。

example.ex: The committee is stacked with members from energy-producing states.
example.tran: 该委员会中安插进了几位来自能源生产州的成员。

value.tran: 在(某组织机构中)安插(对自己有利的人员)

value.boxu_tran: stack 通常表示由扁平物体直接叠放而成的整齐的一叠，如：a neat stack of dishes (整齐的一叠盘子)。heap 通常表示杂乱地堆放成小山或土丘状的一堆物品，如：Now, the house is a heap of rubble (现在，这座房子成了一堆瓦砾)。而 pile 则既可以表示整齐的一堆，也可以表示杂乱的一堆，如：a neat pile of clothes (整齐的一叠衣物)。
value.boxu_usage: A stack of things is usually tidy, and often consists of flat objects placed directly on top of each other. ...a neat stack of dishes. A heap of things is usually untidy, and often has the shape of a hill or mound. Now, the house is a heap of rubble. A pile can be tidy or untidy. ...a neat pile of clothes.

value.def: If you say that the odds are stacked against someone, or that particular factors are stacked against them, you mean that they are unlikely to succeed in what they want to do because the conditions are not favourable.

example.ex: The odds are stacked against civilians getting a fair trial...
example.tran: 平民难以得到公正的审判。

example.ex: Everything seems to be stacked against us.
example.tran: 一切好像都对我们不利。
